{"title_page": "Rusthall F.C.", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Rusthall FC\n| image_size = 160px\n| fullname = Rusthall Football Club\n| nickname = The Rustics<ref name=\"Non-league UK\"/>\n| founded = 1899<ref name=\"Non-league UK\"/>\n| ground = The Jockey Farm Stadium, Nellington Road, Rusthall, [[Royal Tunbridge Wells]]<ref name=\"KIFL\"/>\n| capacity = \n| chairman = Joe Croker<ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/officials/ Rusthall official website \u2013 Officials] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref>\n| manager = James Anderson <ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html Rusthall official website \u2013 Players & coaches] Accessed 13 August 2013</ref>\n| league = {{English football updater|Rusthall}}\n| season = {{English football updater|Rusthall2}}\n| position = {{English football updater|Rusthall3}}\n| pattern_la1 = _whiteborder\n| pattern_b1 = _whitestripes\n| pattern_ra1 = _whiteborder\n| pattern_sh1 = _whitesides\n| pattern_so1 = _whitetop\n| leftarm1 = 388C2B\n| body1 = 388C2B\n| rightarm1 = 388C2B\n| shorts1 = 388C2B\n| socks1 = 388C2B\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = _whitestripes\n| pattern_ra2 = FF0000\n| leftarm2 = FF0000\n| body2 = FF0000\n| rightarm2 = FF0000\n| shorts2 = FF0000\n| socks2 = FF0000\n| image = Rusthall FC Logo-01.png\n| website = www.rusthallfc.com\n| {{Twitter | id= @FCRusthall }}\n| {{Facebook | id= @rusthallfootballclub }}\n| {{Instagram | id= @rusthallfootballclub }}\n| coordinates = 51.138558\n0.223581\n}}\n\n'''Rusthall F.C.''' is an [[England|English]] [[Association football|football club]] located in [[Rusthall]], near [[Royal Tunbridge Wells]], in [[Kent]]. The club plays in the {{English football updater|Rusthall}}. Rusthall spent most of its history in the Tunbridge Wells League before entering the [[Kent County Football League]] in 1983\u201384. After winning three championships at this level, the club was accepted into the newly formed Kent Invicta Football League for the inaugural 2011\u201312 season.\n\n==History==\nRusthall Football Club was formed in 1899 when they registered with the [[Kent County Football Association]] and entered the Tunbridge Wells League.<ref name=\"Non-league UK\">[http://www.nonleague.co.uk/leagues/index.html/_/kent-invicta/kent-invicta-league-premier/rusthall-r998 Non-league UK \u2013 Rusthall] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref><ref name=\"History\">[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/a/history-9189.html Rusthall official website \u2013 History] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> They won their first silverware in 1904\u201305, winning the league.<ref name=\"History\"/> They won the league a further five times in the 1920s, and a further four times in the 1930s.<ref name=\"History\"/> During this time Rusthall also won four Tunbridge Wells Senior Cups.<ref name=\"History\"/> After the [[Second World War]] they won the league only once more in 1951\u201352 and the Senior Cup twice before entering the [[Kent County Football League]] in 1983.<ref name=\"History\"/><ref name=\"Honours TWSC\">[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/a/honours-10846.html&page=3 Rusthall official website \u2013 Honours TWSC] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> They won the Kent County League Division Two West in their first season, achieving promotion to Division One West, which they also won in their first season.<ref name=\"History\"/> They won the Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup a further six times before winning the West Kent Challenge Shield in 2003\u201304.<ref name=\"History\"/> The following season Rusthall won both Division One West and the Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup, earning promotion to the Premier Division.<ref name=\"History\"/> For the 2011\u201312 season the club was accepted into the Kent Invicta Football League at level 10 of the English football league system for the league's inaugural season.<ref name=\"fchd\">{{fchd|name=RUSTHALL|id=RUSTHALL}}</ref>\n\nFlood lights were installed in April 2016 allowing evening games to be played and play in the FA Vase.\n\nRusthall gained promotion to the [[Southern Counties East Football League]] Premier Division as Division One runners-up during the [[2016-17 Southern Counties East Football League|2016\u201317 season]]. They also competed in their first ever FA Cup game against [[CB Hounslow United F.C.|CB Hounslow United]] in the extra preliminary round of the [[2017\u201318 FA Cup qualifying rounds|2017\u201318 FA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rusthallfc.com/news/fa-cup-vs-cb-hounslow-united-fc-1879206.html|title=FA Cup: vs CB Hounslow United FC - News - Rusthall Football Club|website=www.rusthallfc.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref>\n\n==Colours==\nRusthall's colours are green and white striped shirts, with green shorts and socks.<ref name=\"KIFL\">[http://www.kentinvictaleague.com/clubs/Rusthall.php Kent Invicta League official website \u2013 Rusthall] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> The away kit is red and white striped shirts, with red shorts and socks.<ref name=\"KIFL\"/>\n\n==Grounds==\nRusthall play their home games at The Jockey Farm Stadium, Nellington Road, Rusthall, Tunbridge Wells, Kent, TN4 8SH.  Before the 1980s the club played at Southwood Road, but moved to Jockey Farm in order to meet ground grading criteria.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\n==Management team/staff==\n*Manager - James Anderson<ref>{{cite web|title=Gary Sharman Profile|url=http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=945059|publisher=Rusthall FC|accessdate=15 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130815123836/http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=945059|archivedate=15 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Keith Saxon Profile|url=http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=961198|publisher=Rusthall FC|accessdate=15 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130815123847/http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=961198|archivedate=15 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\nRusthall has won three league championships and one cup in its time in the Kent County League, and eleven league championships and thirteen cups at the Tunbridge Wells level.<ref name=\"History\"/><ref name=\"Honours TWSC\"/><ref>[http://www.kentcountyfootballleague.co.uk/history.asp Kent County Football League \u2013 History] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120602013838/http://www.kentcountyfootballleague.co.uk/history.asp |date=2012-06-02 }} Accessed 21 January 2012</ref>\n* Southern Counties East Division One<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rusthallfc.com/news/promotion-confirmed-1785354.html|title=PROMOTION CONFIRMED! - News - Rusthall Football Club|website=www.rusthallfc.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref>: Runners-up 2016\u201317\n* [[Kent County League]] Division One West<ref name=\"fchd\" />: Champions 1984\u201385, 2004\u201305\n* County League Division Two West: Champions 1983\u201384\n* Kent County League Senior Division West Challenge Cup: Runners-up 1987\u201388\n* West Kent Challenge Shield: Winners 2003\u201304\n* Tunbridge Wells League: Champions 1904\u201305, 1922\u201323, 1923\u201324, 1924\u201325, 1925\u201326, 1929\u201330, 1930\u201331, 1934\u201335, 1937\u201338, 1938\u201339, 1951\u201352\n* Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup:Winners 1929\u201330, 1930\u201331, 1934\u201335, 1937\u201338, 1954\u201355, 1959\u201360, 1992\u201393, 1993\u201394, 1994\u201395, 2000\u201301, 2002\u201303, 2003\u201304, 2004\u201305{{cn|date=June 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.rusthallfc.com/}}\n* {{official Twitter|http://www.twitter.com/FCRusthall/}}\n* {{official Facebook|http://www.facebook.com/rusthallfootballclub/}}\n* {{official Instagram|http://www.instagram.com/rusthallfootballclub/}}\n\n{{Kent Invicta League}}\n\n{{Coord|51.13856|N|0.223593|E|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in England]]\n[[Category:Kent Invicta Football League]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Kent]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1899]]\n[[Category:1899 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Sport in Royal Tunbridge Wells]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Rusthall FC\n| image_size = 160px\n| fullname = Rusthall Football Club\n| nickname = The Rustics<ref name=\"Non-league UK\"/>\n| founded = 1899<ref name=\"Non-league UK\"/>\n| ground = The Jockey Farm Stadium, Nellington Road, Rusthall, [[Royal Tunbridge Wells]]<ref name=\"KIFL\"/>\n| capacity = \n| chairman = Joe Croker<ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/officials/ Rusthall official website \u2013 Officials] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref>\n| manager = James Anderson <ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html Rusthall official website \u2013 Players & coaches] Accessed 13 August 2013</ref>\n| league = {{English football updater|Rusthall}}\n| season = {{English football updater|Rusthall2}}\n| position = {{English football updater|Rusthall3}}\n| pattern_la1 = _whiteborder\n| pattern_b1 = _whitestripes\n| pattern_ra1 = _whiteborder\n| pattern_sh1 = _whitesides\n| pattern_so1 = _whitetop\n| leftarm1 = 388C2B\n| body1 = 388C2B\n| rightarm1 = 388C2B\n| shorts1 = 388C2B\n| socks1 = 388C2B\n| pattern_la2 = \n| pattern_b2 = _whitestripes\n| pattern_ra2 = FF0000\n| leftarm2 = FF0000\n| body2 = FF0000\n| rightarm2 = FF0000\n| shorts2 = FF0000\n| socks2 = FF0000\n| image = Rusthall FC Logo-01.png\n| website = www.rusthallfc.com\n| {{Twitter | id= @FCRusthall }}\n| {{Facebook | id= @rusthallfootballclub }}\n| {{Instagram | id= @rusthallfootballclub }}\n| coordinates = 51.138558\n0.223581\n}}\n\n'''Rusthall F.C.''' is an [[England|English]] [[Association football|football club]] located in [[Rusthall]], near [[Royal Tunbridge Wells]], in [[Kent]]. The club plays in the {{English football updater|Rusthall}}. Rusthall spent most of its history in the Tunbridge Wells League before entering the [[Kent County Football League]] in 1983\u201384. After winning three championships at this level, the club was accepted into the newly formed Kent Invicta Football League for the inaugural 2011\u201312 season.\n\n==History==\nRusthall Football Club was formed in 1899 when they registered with the [[Kent County Football Association]] and entered the Tunbridge Wells League.<ref name=\"Non-league UK\">[http://www.nonleague.co.uk/leagues/index.html/_/kent-invicta/kent-invicta-league-premier/rusthall-r998 Non-league UK \u2013 Rusthall] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref><ref name=\"History\">[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/a/history-9189.html Rusthall official website \u2013 History] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> They won their first silverware in 1904\u201305, winning the league.<ref name=\"History\"/> They won the league a further five times in the 1920s, and a further four times in the 1930s.<ref name=\"History\"/> During this time Rusthall also won four Tunbridge Wells Senior Cups.<ref name=\"History\"/> After the [[Second World War]] they won the league only once more in 1951\u201352 and the Senior Cup twice before entering the [[Kent County Football League]] in 1983.<ref name=\"History\"/><ref name=\"Honours TWSC\">[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/a/honours-10846.html&page=3 Rusthall official website \u2013 Honours TWSC] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> They won the Kent County League Division Two West in their first season, achieving promotion to Division One West, which they also won in their first season.<ref name=\"History\"/> They won the Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup a further six times before winning the West Kent Challenge Shield in 2003\u201304.<ref name=\"History\"/> The following season Rusthall won both Division One West and the Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup, earning promotion to the Premier Division.<ref name=\"History\"/> For the 2011\u201312 season the club was accepted into the Kent Invicta Football League at level 10 of the English football league system for the league's inaugural season.<ref name=\"fchd\">{{fchd|name=RUSTHALL|id=RUSTHALL}}</ref>\n\nFlood lights were installed in April 2016 allowing evening games to be played and play in the FA Vase.\n\nRusthall gained promotion to the [[Southern Counties East Football League]] Premier Division as Division One runners-up during the [[2016-17 Southern Counties East Football League|2016\u201317 season]]. They also competed in their first ever FA Cup game against [[CB Hounslow United F.C.|CB Hounslow United]] in the extra preliminary round of the [[2017\u201318 FA Cup qualifying rounds|2017\u201318 FA Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rusthallfc.com/news/fa-cup-vs-cb-hounslow-united-fc-1879206.html|title=FA Cup: vs CB Hounslow United FC - News - Rusthall Football Club|website=www.rusthallfc.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref>\n\n==Colours==\nRusthall's colours are green and white striped shirts, with green shorts and socks.<ref name=\"KIFL\">[http://www.kentinvictaleague.com/clubs/Rusthall.php Kent Invicta League official website \u2013 Rusthall] Accessed 21 January 2012</ref> The away kit is red and white striped shirts, with red shorts and socks.<ref name=\"KIFL\"/>\n\n==Grounds==\nRusthall play their home games at The Jockey Farm Stadium, Nellington Road, Rusthall, Tunbridge Wells, Kent, TN4 8SH.  Before the 1980s the club played at Southwood Road, but moved to Jockey Farm in order to meet ground grading criteria.<ref name=\"History\"/>\n\n==Management team/staff==\n*Manager - James Anderson<ref>{{cite web|title=Gary Sharman Profile|url=http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=945059|publisher=Rusthall FC|accessdate=15 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130815123836/http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=945059|archivedate=15 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Keith Saxon Profile|url=http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=961198|publisher=Rusthall FC|accessdate=15 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130815123847/http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/rusthallfootballclub/s/players-coaches-27502.html?player_id=961198|archivedate=15 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\nRusthall has won three league championships and one cup in its time in the Kent County League, and eleven league championships and thirteen cups at the Tunbridge Wells level.<ref name=\"History\"/><ref name=\"Honours TWSC\"/><ref>[http://www.kentcountyfootballleague.co.uk/history.asp Kent County Football League \u2013 History] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120602013838/http://www.kentcountyfootballleague.co.uk/history.asp |date=2012-06-02 }} Accessed 21 January 2012</ref>\n* Southern Counties East Division One<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rusthallfc.com/news/promotion-confirmed-1785354.html|title=PROMOTION CONFIRMED! - News - Rusthall Football Club|website=www.rusthallfc.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref>: Runners-up 2016\u201317\n* [[Kent County League]] Division One West<ref name=\"fchd\" />: Champions 1984\u201385, 2004\u201305\n* County League Division Two West: Champions 1983\u201384\n* Kent County League Senior Division West Challenge Cup: Runners-up 1987\u201388\n* West Kent Challenge Shield: Winners 2003\u201304\n* Tunbridge Wells League: Champions 1904\u201305, 1922\u201323, 1923\u201324, 1924\u201325, 1925\u201326, 1929\u201330, 1930\u201331, 1934\u201335, 1937\u201338, 1938\u201339, 1951\u201352\n* Tunbridge Wells Senior Cup:Winners 1929\u201330, 1930\u201331, 1934\u201335, 1937\u201338, 1954\u201355, 1959\u201360, 1992\u201393, 1993\u201394, 1994\u201395, 2000\u201301, 2002\u201303, 2003\u201304, 2004\u201305{{cn|date=June 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.rusthallfc.com/}}\n{{official Twitter|http://www.twitter.com/FCRusthall/}}\n{{official Facebook|http://www.facebook.com/rusthallfootballclub/}}\n{{official Instagram|http://www.instagram.com/rusthallfootballclub/}}\n\n{{Kent Invicta League}}\n\n{{Coord|51.13856|N|0.223593|E|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in England]]\n[[Category:Kent Invicta Football League]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in Kent]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1899]]\n[[Category:1899 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Sport in Royal Tunbridge Wells]]\n", "name_user": "Jamie1986p", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rusthall_F.C."}
{"title_page": "John Campbell (Ontario politician)", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name         = John Campbell\n| image        = John Campbell May 2018.jpg\n| imagesize    = \n| caption      = \n| office1      = [[Toronto City Council]]lor for [[Islington-City Centre West|Ward 4 (Etobicoke Centre)]]\n| term_start1  = December 1, 2014\n| term_end1    = December 1, 2018\n| predecessor1 = [[Gloria Lindsay Luby]]\n| successor1   = Ward Abolished\n| office2       = [[Toronto District School Board|Toronto Public School Trustee]] for [[Etobicoke Centre (provincial electoral district)|(Ward 2) Etobicoke Centre]]\n| term_start2   = December 1, 2003\n| term_end2 = December 1, 2010\n| predecessor2 =\n| successor2 = [[Chris Glover]]\n| birth_date   =\n| birth_place  = \n| residence    = \n| religion     = \n| nationality  = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| spouse       = \n| occupation   = marketing consultant\n}}\n\n'''John Campbell''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] politician, who was elected to [[Toronto City Council]] in the [[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 municipal election]].<ref name=wins>[https://www.thestar.com/news/city_hall/toronto2014election/2014/10/27/john_campbell_wins_ward_4_etobicoke_centre.html \"John Campbell wins Ward 4, Etobicoke Centre\"]. ''[[Toronto Star]]'', October 27, 2014.</ref>\n\nHe represented [[Islington-City Centre West|Ward 4 (Etobicoke Centre)]] from 2014\u20132018.  During his term of office he served on many high-profile Council Committees and City agencies including the Budget Committee, the Planning Growth Management Committee and the Toronto Transit Commission.<ref>https://www.ttc.ca/News/2014/December/New_TTC_Board_appointed.jsp</ref><ref>http://app.toronto.ca/tmmis/viewAgendaItemHistory.do?item=2015.ST1.1</ref>\n   \nCampbell is a graduate of the University of Toronto (Political Science and Economics). He earned an MBA from the Schulich School of Business (Finance and Strategic Management) after four and a half years of evening study in 1999.<ref>http://johnfcampbell.ca/about</ref>\n\nHe ran for Councillor in the newly formed Ward 2 Etobicoke Centre in the [[2018 Toronto municipal election|2018 Toronto election]] and lost by a small margin to [[Stephen Holyday]].<ref>https://www.thestar.com/news/toronto-election/2018/10/22/stephen-holyday-defeats-fellow-incumbent-john-campbell-in-ward-2-etobicoke-centre.html</ref>\n\nPrior to his election as Councillor in 2014, Campbell worked as a sales and marketing consultant, and was a trustee and chair of the [[Toronto District School Board]].<ref name=wins/>\n\nHe ran for councillor in  [[Islington-City Centre West|Ward 4 (Etobicoke Centre)]] in the [[2010 Toronto municipal election|2010 election]], losing narrowly to incumbent councillor [[Gloria Lindsay Luby]].<ref name=wins/>\n\n==Electoral record==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|'''[[2018 Toronto municipal election|2018 Toronto election]], Ward 2'''<ref name=\"City of Toronto elections page\">[http://election.toronto.ca/epr2014/eprDetail.do?C;003,102,302,204,403, City of Toronto elections page]</ref> \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"150px\" | Candidate\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | Votes\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\"  | %\n|-\n|'''Stephen Holyday''' ||align=right|14,627 ||align=right|38.58% \n|-\n|'''John Campbell''' ||align=right| 13,441 ||align=right| 35.45% \n|-\n|Angelo Carnvale||align=right| 5,735 ||align=right| 15.13%\n|-\n|Erica Kelly ||align=right| 3,854 ||align=right| 10.16% \n|-\n|Bill Boersma ||align=right| 258 ||align=right| .68%\n|-\n!Total||align=right| 37,555 ||align=right| 100% \n|}\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"8\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|Colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"|'''[[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 Toronto election]], Ward 4'''<ref name=\"City of Toronto elections page\"/> \n|-\n! bgcolor=\"#DDDDFF\" width=\"150px\" | Ca